com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator

Class PropagatorAbstractAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.impl.AdapterImpl
      • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator.AbstractAdapter
        • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator.PropagatorAbstractAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Adapter, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Adapter.Internal
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PropagatorDependencyAdapter, PropagatorFunctionAdapter

    public class PropagatorAbstractAdapter
extends AbstractAdapter
    The base class of the propagators used by the framework. Implements the binding with the data elements. There are two kinds of bindings: inbound and outbound binding. An inbound binding binds the PropagatorFunctionAdapter to some input data element while an outbond binding binds the PropagatorFunctionAdapter to some output data element.

    Inbound bindings listen to changes in the target object of this adapter by implementing the method PropagatorAbstractAdapter.InboundBinding.notifyChanged(Notification) and call PropagatorAbstractAdapter.InboundBinding.touch() when some change in the bound feature occurred.

    Outbound bindings implement the method PropagatorAbstractAdapter.OutboundBinding.isOutboundBinding(Object), allowing the framework to query if if some feature of this adapter is set (bound) by the PropagatorFunctionAdapter.

    Two standard inbound bindings are provided. A PropagatorAbstractAdapter.InboundBindingFeature, binding to some feature of this propagator's Notifier and a PropagatorAbstractAdapter.InboundBindingNavigationFeature, binding to some navigation feature , and propagating the binding to the referred object by receiving a PropagatorDependencyAdapter. These standards Inbound binding can be added with the convenience methods addInboundBindingFeature(Object) and addInboundBindingNavigationFeature(Object, Object) respectively.

    One standard outbound binding is provided. An PropagatorAbstractAdapter.OutboundBindingFeature, binding to some feature of this propagator's Notifier. This standards Outbound binding can be added with the convenience methods addOutboundBindingFeature(Object).

    Registering the PropagatorDependencyAdapters is done by the method PropagatorAbstractAdapter.InboundBinding.addDependencyAdapters(), called when this adapter is added to the notifier. Unregistering the PropagatorDependencyAdapters is done by the method PropagatorAbstractAdapter.InboundBinding.removeDependencyAdapters(), called when the adapter is removed from the Notifier.

    michel
